div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES, FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION
In the Matter of teh Application of CHIN QUOCK WAH, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. ) No. 2971 MOTION.

Comes now the Petitioner Chin Quock Wah, through his attorneys Beeler and Sullivan, and respectfully moves this Honorable Court, that a Writ of Habeas Corpus be issued out of this Court and have an order to Show Cause on the United States Commissioner of Immigration, the Honorable Henry M. White, or on such other person or persons acting under or through him or acting for the United States Government, why the said Petitioner Chin Quock Wah is imprisoned, confined and restrained and why he should not be released and permitted to have his liberty.

This motion is based upon the Further Amended Petition, verified by Adam Beeler of the Law Firm of Beeler and Sullivan as counsel for the said Petitioner and upon all of the records and files in this cause.
